 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNESBURG - Newly-appointed Bafana Bafana head coach Stuart Baxter is making his first official address at the Safa House.Baxter is expected to outline his plans for the national team ahead of the Africa Cup of Nations qualifier against Nigeria in June.Supersport United FC and the South African Football Association (Safa) agreed to terms on the release of Baxter from SuperSport United to Bafana Bafana at the end of the current PSL.The Supersport United coach will continue to fulfil his coaching responsibilities at the club for the remaining four Absa Premiership fixtures as well as the Nedbank Cup and Confederations Cup.READ: Baxter named new Bafana coachSafa and Supersport United have agreed to work together to ensure that Baxter gets time off post the final league match on 27 May to prepare Bafana Bafana for the upcoming AFCON match against Nigeria.The Senior Men s National Team takes on the Super Eagles on the weekend of 9-11 in Nigeria.Baxter joined Supersport United in January 2016 and led Matsatsantsa to a Top 8 finish and won them the Nedbank Cup trophy with a victory over Orlando Pirates on May 2016.This season Supersport United reached the Telkom Cup Final and will face Chippa United in the Nedbank Cup semi-final on the 20 May.African News Agency